        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/aca169/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-06-06T12:25:08.717Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Signal occupies a lot of space on my device. Thus, I would like to remove a lot of media at once. However, I can only select all of them or select single images or videos. This is not convenient, if you would like to delete half of all images, for example.</p>\n<p>Most file managers offer to select the first and the last item to be deleted and a button that will automatically select all the items in between. Then, it would be easy to delete the right number of media files in Signal.</p>",
