        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/picob/{size}/589_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-06-06T13:11:42.887Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Please keep in mind that when deleting media, you‚Äôll also <strong>lose any text associated with the media</strong> (for messages containing text and media). See here for details:</p><aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"2680\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/picob/48/589_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/media-deletion-keep-message-text-dont-delete-whole-message/2680\">Media deletion: Keep message text / don't delete whole message</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    Hi folks, \nas Greyson Parrelli (from the Signal Team) stated in <a href=\"https://github.com/signalapp/Signal-Android/pull/7722#issuecomment-383729968\">a GitHub comment</a>, \n\ndeleting [‚Ä¶] media (via the media viewer, or ‚Äúall media‚Äù screen) will also delete the message itself. \n\nWell, I can confirm this, but that was not what (I guess) someone is expecting when you‚Äôre going to delete media, since the media technically (and IMHO logically as well) is just a part of the message and should be handled appropriately (like anywhere else, e. g. when copying messages, creating backups etc.). T‚Ä¶\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
